Reasoning: The paper focuses on a framework for performance experimentation with dense linear algebra kernels, algorithms, and libraries. This falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and performance evaluation (cs.PF). The framework also allows for experiments to be run on a range of architectures, including clusters and supercomputers, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Python scripts to design experiments, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper emphasizes the practical value of the framework in supporting critical performance decisions, which could fall under the category of modeling and simulation (cs.MS).
